<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-04-25T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-04-25T19:00:00-05:00" n="755" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d755">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">890F. 51A/4: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Minister Resident in Saudi Arabia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Moose</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-04-25T20:00:00-04:00">April
                                        25, 1944—8 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>69. During your forthcoming talks with the King you may state, if it
                                appears advisable to do so, as suggested in your 116, April 20, 1
                                p.m., that if King Ibn Saud would like to have American advisers in
                                a military, financial or other capacity, sympathetic consideration
                                will be given to his request.</p>
                            <p>It appears desirable that Eddy remain in Riyadh if it is feasible to
                                arrange for him to do so.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>